<body>

    <h1>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h1>

    <div class="faq-container">
        <div class="faq">
            <h2>What is the purpose of this platform?</h2>
            <p>This platform is designed for students to upload their project files, view their submissions, and manage their portfolios. It allows students to easily share their project details and files for evaluation.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>How do I register on the platform?</h2>
            <p>To register, click on the "Sign Up" button on the homepage. You will need to provide your name, student email, password, and other required details. Once registered, you can log in and upload your projects.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>What should I do if I forget my password?</h2>
            <p>If you forget your password, you can click on the "Forgot Password" link on the login page. Follow the instructions to reset your password using your registered email address.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>Can I update my project after submitting it?</h2>
            <p>Yes, you can update your project submission by logging in and editing the project details. If you need to replace the file, make sure to upload the new version after making the changes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq">
            <h2>Who can view my submitted project?</h2>
            <p>Your submitted project will be visible to the faculty or admins overseeing the project evaluations. However, the general public will not have access to your project details unless you choose to share it.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
